==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{m|enm|befallen}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|befeallan||to fall, deprive of, bereave of, fall to, be assigned to, befall}}, equivalent to {{prefix|be|fall|lang=en}}. Cognate with Dutch {{m|nl|bevallen||to please}}, German {{m|de|befallen||to befall, attack, overcome}}, Swedish {{m|sv|befalla||to command, prescribe, direct}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}}: {{IPA|/bɪˈfɔːl/|lang=en}}
* {{a|US}}: {{IPA|/bɪˈfɔl/|lang=en}}, {{IPA|/bɪˈfɑl/|lang=en}}
* {{audio|En-us-befall.ogg|Audio (US)|lang=en}}
* {{rhymes|ɔːl|lang=en}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb|befalls|befalling|befell|befallen}}

# {{lb|en|transitive}} To [[fall]] upon; fall all over; [[overtake]]
#: At dusk an unusual calm '''befalls''' the wetlands.
# {{label|en|intransitive}} To [[happen]].
# {{label|en|transitive}} To happen to.
#: ''Temptation '''befell''' me.''
